🌿 They thought it was dye.
But every print you see? It’s the imprint of a real leaf.

Plucked, bundled, steamed, and unwrapped — this is the story of how nature writes itself onto fabric.

From Santiniketan’s trees to your hands, every Dori saree carries a quiet kind of magic.

👇 Which part of this process surprised you the most?
Drop your thoughts below — we read every one.

latestPosts.caption:
|| 🌾 MATI RAAG 🌱 ||
Song of Earth Painted in Kalamkari

Five stories.
Five journeys.

A graceful soul @ajoy_jana_ who embraces both softness and strength, dancing freely in a world still learning acceptance.
————————————————-
A spirited young dancer @rinky_das09 whose steps rise above the limitations of society .
————————————————-
A woman @amritasenguptakolkata who moves between the runway and her kitchen, embodying elegance in both — a model, a muse.
————————————————
A mother @aninditaroy290 in her late 50s who has weathered storms, worn silence like armor, and now stands unshaken — timeless, tender, and true.
————————————————
And @woman_in_buddha_jeanss a teacher and a dream-weaver — shaping Gutipoca with purpose and pride, #celebratingeverycurve , #everyscar , #everyshadeofwomanhood.

#Differentlives.
#Differentbeginnings.

But in this moment, they stand together — draped in ||🌾Mati Raag🌱|| — the earth’s quiet song of #inclusion , #resilience , and #belonging .

Because the soil welcomes all. And so do we.

🌱 This is more than #Kalamkari.
It is story.
It is soil.
It is strength. 

📸: @click_with_sb

Casting dazing light 🔦 on our new series:
||🌾 Mati Raag 🌱||
————————————————
Two women. Two worlds.

One @aninditaroy290 : Her life marked by silent storms and quiet courage. 

Another @amritasenguptakolkata : Her life shaped by independence, ambition, and unapologetic selfhood.
————————————————————————
They do not mirror each other.
But they see each other.
In their differences lies their power.
In their stories—grit, grace, and the right to define womanhood on their own terms.
